CancelMatchmakingTicketRequest.name: CancelMatchmakingTicketRequest
CancelMatchmakingTicketRequest.description:
Only servers and ticket members can cancel a ticket.

                The ticket can be in four different states when it is cancelled.
                1: the ticket is waiting for members to join it, and it has not started matching.
                    If the ticket is cancelled at this stage, it will never match.
                2: the ticket is matching. If the ticket is cancelled, it will stop matching.
                3: the ticket is matched. A matched ticket cannot be cancelled.
                4: the ticket is already cancelled and nothing happens.

                There may be race conditions between the ticket getting matched and
                the client making a cancellation request. The client must handle the possibility
                that the cancel request fails if a match is found before the cancellation request is processed.
                We do not allow resubmitting a cancelled ticket because players
                must consent to enter matchmaking again. Create a new ticket instead.

GetQueueStatisticsRequest.name: GetQueueStatisticsRequest
GetQueueStatisticsRequest.description:
Returns the matchmaking statistics for a queue. These include the number of players matching
                and the statistics related to the time to match statistics in seconds (average and percentiles).
                Statistics are refreshed once every 5 minutes.

                Servers can access all statistics no matter what the ClientStatisticsVisibility is configured to.
                Clients can access statistics according to the ClientStatisticsVisibility.
                Client requests are forbidden if all visibility fields are false.

properties.name: QueueName
properties.description: The name of the queue.

properties.name: NumberOfPlayersMatching
properties.description: The current number of players in the matchmaking queue, who are waiting to be matched.

properties.name: TimeToMatchStatisticsInSeconds
properties.description: Statistics representing the time (in seconds) it takes for tickets to find a match.

JoinMatchmakingTicketRequest.name: JoinMatchmakingTicketRequest
JoinMatchmakingTicketRequest.description:
Add the player to a matchmaking ticket and specify all of its matchmaking
                attributes. Players can join a ticket if and only if their EntityKeys are
                already listed in the ticket's Members list.

                The matchmaking service automatically starts matching the ticket against
                other matchmaking tickets once all players have joined the ticket.
                It is not possible to join a ticket once it has started matching.

properties.name: Member
properties.description: The User who wants to join the ticket. Their Id must be listed in PlayFabIdsToMatchWith.

properties.name: QueueName
properties.description: The Id of the queue to join.

properties.name: TicketId
properties.description: The Id of the ticket to find a match for.

calls.name: CancelMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Cancel a matchmaking ticket.
calls.requestDetails: Only servers and ticket members can cancel a ticket. The ticket can be in four different states when it is cancelled. 1: the ticket is waiting for members to join it, and it has not started matching. If the ticket is cancelled at this stage, it will never match. 2: the ticket is matching. If the ticket is cancelled, it will stop matching. 3: the ticket is matched. A matched ticket cannot be cancelled. 4: the ticket is already cancelled and nothing happens. There may be race conditions between the ticket getting matched and the client making a cancellation request. The client must handle the possibility that the cancel request fails if a match is found before the cancellation request is processed. We do not allow resubmitting a cancelled ticket because players must consent to enter matchmaking again. Create a new ticket instead.

calls.name: GetQueueStatistics
calls.summary: Get the statistics for a queue.
calls.requestDetails: Returns the matchmaking statistics for a queue. These include the number of players matching and the statistics related to the time to match statistics in seconds (average and percentiles). Statistics are refreshed once every 5 minutes. Servers can access all statistics no matter what the ClientStatisticsVisibility is configured to. Clients can access statistics according to the ClientStatisticsVisibility. Client requests are forbidden if all visibility fields are false.

The matchmaking service automatically starts matching the ticket against other matchmaking tickets once all players have joined the ticket. It is not possible to join a ticket once it has started matching.
